items.synopsis: Australia is trying to go big in its first innings after sending England in to bat on day one of the final Ashes Test at the Oval. Follow live.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well, could that session have gone much worse for Australia? Probably not. Five wickets lost, England rediscovering their mojo with a ball that is doing plenty, swinging and seaming all over the joint. Joe Root has only bowled six overs but has done a job for his skipper to get a wicket and hold up an end for a bit, but the real stars have been Stuart Broad and Jimmy Anderson with their excellent start - plus the undervalued Chris Woakes and hardworking Mark Wood. It's still all to play for, but Australia needs to get a fair bit closer to England's first innings total - they still trail by 97.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Tea: Australia 7-186 (Smith 40, Cummins 1)

children.content: Well, could that session have gone much worse for Australia?
Five wickets lost, England rediscovering their mojo with a ball that is doing plenty, swinging and seaming all over the joint.

Joe Root has only bowled six overs but has done a job for his skipper to get a wicket and hold up an end for a bit, but the real stars have been Stuart Broad and Jimmy Anderson with their excellent start - plus the undervalued Chris Woakes and hardworking Mark Wood.
It's still all to play for, but Australia needs to get a fair bit closer to England's first innings total - they still trail by 97.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Starc attempts a pull and doesn't fully commit, a top edge goes straight up in the air and the ball is caught by Ben Duckett at backward square leg. Good pace bowling from Wood, using the bouncer as a shock and awe tactic rather than just pounding away with it.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: STARC IS OUT!

children.content: Starc attempts a pull and doesn't fully commit, a top edge goes straight up in the air and the ball is caught by Ben Duckett at backward square leg.
Good pace bowling from Wood, using the bouncer as a shock and awe tactic rather than just pounding away with it.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Oh that's a poor from Carey! He's handed Ben Stokes his 100th Test catch by just slapping the ball to him at catching wide mid off - exactly where he was placed for that exact shot. Carey actually turned and started walking before the ball was even in Stokes' hands. "That's poor, that's no good," says Ian Healy on Channel 9. Correct. He was sucked into that by Joe Root and he goes for 10.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: OUT! CAREY GOES!

children.content: Oh that's a poor from Carey!
He's handed Ben Stokes his 100th Test catch by just slapping the ball to him at catching wide mid off - exactly where he was placed for that exact shot.
Carey actually turned and started walking before the ball was even in Stokes' hands.
"That's poor, that's no good," says Ian Healy on Channel 9.
He was sucked into that by Joe Root and he goes for 10.
